  "title": "Technical Project Engineer | Precision Engineering | Medical Devices",
  "description": "<p><strong>Our client is a listed company in Precision Engineering and Manufacturing industry. Due to business needs, they are now recruiting a Project & Program Engineer to be part of their Engineering Team for ongoing transformation projects. They are located in the East Area - easily accessible.</strong><br /></p><p><strong>Duties of Project & Program Engineer:</strong></p><ul><li>Plan, manage, and track precision engineering projects, including schedules, budgets, and deliverables.</li><li>Provide technical expertise in CNC machining, micro-fabrication, metrology, and prototype development.</li><li>Ensure compliance with stringent quality and tolerance standards through testing and validation.</li><li>Act as the key liaison with clients, suppliers, and internal teams, preparing progress and risk reports.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Engineering</li><li>3 – 5 years’ relevant project experience in precision manufacturing, or in similar setting handling medical devices clients</li><li>Exposure to CNC Machining is a bonus</li></ul><p><br /></p><p>Interested candidates who wish to apply for the advertised position, please click <strong>APPLY NOW</strong> or email an updated copy of your resume / cv.</p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidate will be notified.</p><ul><li><strong>Email Address: jobs@recruitpedia.sg</strong></li><li>Recruitpedia Pte. Ltd.</li><li>EA License No. 19C9682</li><li>EA Reg. No. R22108850 (Chan Mun Mun)</li></ul>",
